Prepositional modification on theme noun (in tail).
Despite an identical intermediate representation in a recursive/tree-based model of
grammar, baseline Encoder-Decoder Transformers (e.g. Wu et al baseline 2 layer) trained
from scratch on generating logical forms for a corpus including the first type of sentence
but not the second, cannot reliably generalize to doing so for the second type of sentence
(suggests cannot understand the second type of sentence after learning first).
